<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Architecture Decision Records on Zaba505's Home Lab</title><link>https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/adrs/</link><description>Recent content in Architecture Decision Records on Zaba505's Home Lab</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><atom:link href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/adrs/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[0001] Public/Private Infrastructure Split</title><link>https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/adrs/0001-public-private-infrastructure-split/</link><pubDate>Mon, 27 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/adrs/0001-public-private-infrastructure-split/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parent capability:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/"&gt;Self-Hosted Application Platform&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Addresses requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-27"&gt;TR-27&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-01"&gt;TR-01&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-02"&gt;TR-02&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-03"&gt;TR-03&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-05"&gt;TR-05&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-17"&gt;TR-17&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-22"&gt;TR-22&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-32"&gt;TR-32&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-33"&gt;TR-33&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="context"&gt;Context and Problem Statement&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-27"&gt;TR-27&lt;/a&gt; forces the platform to span public-cloud and private/home-lab infrastructure, with the connectivity between them part of the foundation. The capability rule that grounds this — &lt;em&gt;&amp;ldquo;self-hosted means the operator controls end-to-end, not that every component runs on hardware the operator owns&amp;rdquo;&lt;/em&gt; — leaves the &lt;em&gt;split&lt;/em&gt; unspecified: any of the platform&amp;rsquo;s offerings (TR-01 compute, TR-02 storage, TR-03 reachability, TR-04 identity, TR-05 backup, TR-06 observability) may be placed on either side.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[0002] Compute Substrate</title><link>https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/adrs/0002-compute-substrate/</link><pubDate>Mon, 27 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/adrs/0002-compute-substrate/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parent capability:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/"&gt;Self-Hosted Application Platform&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Addresses requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-01"&gt;TR-01&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-12"&gt;TR-12&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-13"&gt;TR-13&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-17"&gt;TR-17&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-19"&gt;TR-19&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-20"&gt;TR-20&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-22"&gt;TR-22&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-24"&gt;TR-24&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-25"&gt;TR-25&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-26"&gt;TR-26&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-32"&gt;TR-32&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-33"&gt;TR-33&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="context"&gt;Context and Problem Statement&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/adrs/0001-public-private-infrastructure-split/"&gt;ADR-0001&lt;/a&gt; places tenant compute on the home-lab side. This ADR picks the substrate that actually runs tenant workloads there. It is the single biggest downstream constraint in this design: it dictates what tenant packaging form is plausible (ADR #3), how the migration runner is built (ADR #10), what observability and identity hooks are available (ADRs #5, #8), and how per-tenant isolation (TR-32) is enforced.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[0003] Tenant Packaging Form</title><link>https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/adrs/0003-tenant-packaging-form/</link><pubDate>Mon, 27 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/adrs/0003-tenant-packaging-form/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parent capability:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/"&gt;Self-Hosted Application Platform&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Addresses requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-10"&gt;TR-10&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-11"&gt;TR-11&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-12"&gt;TR-12&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-22"&gt;TR-22&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-24"&gt;TR-24&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-26"&gt;TR-26&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-31"&gt;TR-31&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-32"&gt;TR-32&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="context"&gt;Context and Problem Statement&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/adrs/0002-compute-substrate/"&gt;ADR-0002&lt;/a&gt; chose Kubernetes as the compute substrate. That constrains but does not fully decide the tenant packaging form: K8s can accept anything from &amp;ldquo;an OCI image and we&amp;rsquo;ll write the manifests for you&amp;rdquo; to &amp;ldquo;a full Helm chart&amp;rdquo; to &amp;ldquo;raw Deployment YAML.&amp;rdquo; TR-10 demands one accepted form for tenant components, and that same form must be acceptable for migration-process artifacts (TR-12).&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[0004] Persistent Storage Offering — Block as the Foundational Primitive</title><link>https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/adrs/0004-persistent-storage-offering/</link><pubDate>Mon, 27 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/adrs/0004-persistent-storage-offering/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parent capability:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/"&gt;Self-Hosted Application Platform&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Addresses requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-02"&gt;TR-02&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-05"&gt;TR-05&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-15"&gt;TR-15&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-32"&gt;TR-32&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-33"&gt;TR-33&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="context"&gt;Context and Problem Statement&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/adrs/0001-public-private-infrastructure-split/"&gt;ADR-0001&lt;/a&gt; places bulk persistent storage on the home-lab side. &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/adrs/0002-compute-substrate/"&gt;ADR-0002&lt;/a&gt; chose Kubernetes. This ADR decides what persistent-storage &lt;em&gt;offerings&lt;/em&gt; the platform exposes to tenants and how the eviction-frozen state from &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-15"&gt;TR-15&lt;/a&gt; works against them.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There is real tension to resolve here. On one side, tenants will need different shapes of storage over time — object stores for media, relational DBs for transactional data, possibly graph or time-series later. On the other side, the parent capability&amp;rsquo;s &lt;em&gt;evolves with its tenants&lt;/em&gt; rule says the platform should grow when tenants need it, not before. Adding three managed offerings up front, ahead of any tenant who needs them, fails that rule by going ahead of the tenants and inflates &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-33"&gt;TR-33&lt;/a&gt; routine maintenance for offerings nobody yet uses.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[0005] Identity Offering — Self-Hosted Authentik</title><link>https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/adrs/0005-identity-offering/</link><pubDate>Mon, 27 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/adrs/0005-identity-offering/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parent capability:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/"&gt;Self-Hosted Application Platform&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Addresses requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-04"&gt;TR-04&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-32"&gt;TR-32&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-17"&gt;TR-17&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-22"&gt;TR-22&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-33"&gt;TR-33&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="context"&gt;Context and Problem Statement&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-04"&gt;TR-04&lt;/a&gt; requires the platform to offer tenants an identity-and-authentication service for &lt;em&gt;their&lt;/em&gt; end users, and constrains that service to be capable of honoring &amp;ldquo;lost credentials cannot be recovered&amp;rdquo; (Signal-style). This is a hard gate: any product that cannot be configured to enforce no-recovery is ineligible.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/adrs/0001-public-private-infrastructure-split/"&gt;ADR-0001&lt;/a&gt; reserves the cloud edge for ingress and the off-site backup archive only, so identity, if self-hosted, lives in the home-lab cluster. &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/adrs/0002-compute-substrate/"&gt;ADR-0002&lt;/a&gt; makes the home-lab a Kubernetes cluster with namespaces as the per-tenant boundary; whatever IdP we choose has to plug into that.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[0006] Network Reachability — Cloudflare Edge to Homelab Cluster</title><link>https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/adrs/0006-network-reachability/</link><pubDate>Mon, 27 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/adrs/0006-network-reachability/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parent capability:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/"&gt;Self-Hosted Application Platform&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Addresses requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-03"&gt;TR-03&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-32"&gt;TR-32&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-22"&gt;TR-22&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-26"&gt;TR-26&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-27"&gt;TR-27&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-28"&gt;TR-28&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-33"&gt;TR-33&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="context"&gt;Context and Problem Statement&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-03"&gt;TR-03&lt;/a&gt; requires the platform to deliver two flavors of reachability — externally for tenants&amp;rsquo; end users and internally between tenants — and &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-32"&gt;TR-32&lt;/a&gt; requires per-tenant isolation strong enough that no tenant can read another&amp;rsquo;s traffic or signals. &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/adrs/0001-public-private-infrastructure-split/"&gt;ADR-0001&lt;/a&gt; set up a small cloud edge for ingress and an off-site backup archive, with a self-hosted VPN between cloud and homelab. &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/adrs/0002-compute-substrate/"&gt;ADR-0002&lt;/a&gt; chose Kubernetes; &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/adrs/0003-tenant-packaging-form/"&gt;ADR-0003&lt;/a&gt; keeps NetworkPolicy / RBAC entirely on the platform side, derived from the tenant-manifest schema rather than shipped by tenants.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[0007] Backup &amp; Disaster Recovery</title><link>https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/adrs/0007-backup-and-disaster-recovery/</link><pubDate>Mon, 27 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/adrs/0007-backup-and-disaster-recovery/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parent capability:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/"&gt;Self-Hosted Application Platform&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Addresses requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-05"&gt;TR-05&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-15"&gt;TR-15&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-22"&gt;TR-22&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-26"&gt;TR-26&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-32"&gt;TR-32&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-33"&gt;TR-33&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="context"&gt;Context and Problem Statement&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-05"&gt;TR-05&lt;/a&gt; requires the platform to back up tenant data and be able to restore it, to a uniform standard the platform defines. This ADR picks the &lt;em&gt;mechanism&lt;/em&gt;, the &lt;em&gt;destination&lt;/em&gt;, the &lt;em&gt;cadence&lt;/em&gt;, and the &lt;em&gt;retention policy&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Two specific surfaces the design has to cover at this ADR&amp;rsquo;s scope:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Block PVCs&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/adrs/0004-persistent-storage-offering/"&gt;ADR-0004&lt;/a&gt;) — the foundational tenant storage primitive. Future managed-storage offerings will each define their own backup semantics in their own ADRs but ride this ADR&amp;rsquo;s destination and retention shape.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Authentik&amp;rsquo;s internal Postgres&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/adrs/0005-identity-offering/"&gt;ADR-0005&lt;/a&gt;) — the platform&amp;rsquo;s own identity state, treated as platform-state (not tenant data) for retention purposes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This ADR also resolves the eviction UX&amp;rsquo;s deferred &lt;em&gt;Open Question&lt;/em&gt; about deeper-backup-tier retention beyond the 30-day tenant-accessible window (&lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/user-experiences/move-off-the-platform-after-eviction/"&gt;UX §Open Questions&lt;/a&gt;). A deliberate retention choice closes that loop.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[0008] Observability Stack — LGTM + OpenTelemetry Collector</title><link>https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/adrs/0008-observability-stack/</link><pubDate>Mon, 27 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/adrs/0008-observability-stack/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parent capability:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/"&gt;Self-Hosted Application Platform&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Addresses requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-06"&gt;TR-06&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-07"&gt;TR-07&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-08"&gt;TR-08&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-09"&gt;TR-09&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-22"&gt;TR-22&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-32"&gt;TR-32&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-33"&gt;TR-33&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="context"&gt;Context and Problem Statement&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Five tightly-coupled responsibilities ride on this ADR:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Standard health bundle&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-06"&gt;TR-06&lt;/a&gt;) — availability, latency, error rate, resource saturation, restart/deployment events — uniformly across tenants.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tenant-scoped access for capability owners; cross-tenant for the operator&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-07"&gt;TR-07&lt;/a&gt;) — one offering, scope enforcement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Self-serve threshold tuning&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-08"&gt;TR-08&lt;/a&gt;) — the only capability-owner self-service surface in the entire platform.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Email push alerting with degraded-delivery indication&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-09"&gt;TR-09&lt;/a&gt;) — alerts go by email; the tenant view must surface when delivery is degraded so silence is not mistaken for health.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tenant isolation&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/tech-requirements/#tr-32"&gt;TR-32&lt;/a&gt;) — no tenant or capability owner can read another tenant&amp;rsquo;s signals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Because the platform&amp;rsquo;s compute is Kubernetes (&lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/adrs/0002-compute-substrate/"&gt;ADR-0002&lt;/a&gt;) and the packaging form is platform-defined (&lt;a href="https://zaba505.github.io/infra/pr-preview/pr-721/capabilities/self-hosted-application-platform/adrs/0003-tenant-packaging-form/"&gt;ADR-0003&lt;/a&gt;), the ingestion contract from tenant pods is a platform decision: tenants emit signals through whatever protocol the platform standardizes on, and the platform fans them into the storage layer.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>